| `<link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">` | External CSS linking | Presentation |
| `background: linear-gradient(...)` | CSS3 gradient function | Presentation |
| `onsubmit="return validateForm()"` | Inline event handler + DOM event | Behavior |
| `document.forms["regForm"]["name"].value` | Form DOM API access | Behavior |
| `/^[^\s@]+@[^\s@]+\.[^\s@]+$/` | Regular expression for email | Behavior |
| `$_SERVER['REQUEST_METHOD']` | PHP superglobal | Logic |
| `htmlspecialchars()` | XSS prevention | Logic (Security) |
| `filter_var(..., FILTER_VALIDATE_EMAIL)` | Built-in PHP filter | Logic (Validation) |

> [!NOTE]
> In your KTU lab record, **always explain why** you used `htmlspecialchars()` and `filter_var()`. Examiners award 2 marks specifically for "security considerations" mentioned in the viva.

