**Q2. [KTU University Exam – Dec 2023, Model]**
*What is the purpose of the `htmlspecialchars()` function in PHP? Why is it essential before echoing user input?*

**Model Answer (3 marks):**

`htmlspecialchars()` is a **built-in PHP function** that converts special HTML characters into their corresponding **HTML entities**. Specifically:

- `<` becomes `&lt;`
- `>` becomes `&gt;`
- `"` becomes `&quot;`
- `'` becomes `&#039;`
- `&` becomes `&amp;`

**Why it is essential:** It prevents **Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)** attacks. Suppose a malicious user enters `<script>alert('hacked')</script>` into the name field. If echoed directly into HTML, the browser would execute the script. By wrapping the input in `htmlspecialchars()`, the tag is displayed as harmless text instead of being executed.

*Real-world example:* `echo htmlspecialchars($_POST['name']);` safely displays the user's name without allowing injected scripts to run.

*(1 mark function purpose, 1 mark conversion examples, 1 mark XSS prevention justification)*

