### 5.3 Topic Recap & Important Things to Remember

- [x] **CSS has three application methods:** Inline, Internal (`<style>`), External (`<link>`).
- [x] **CSS specificity** follows $(a, b, c, d)$ — ID $\gt$ Class $\gt$ Type.
- [x] **`!important` overrides** all specificity rules except other `!important` declarations.
- [x] **JavaScript** runs in the **browser**, is used for client-side **validation, interactivity, and DOM manipulation**.
- [x] **PHP** runs on the **server**, has extension **`.php`**, and uses `<?php ?>` tags.
- [x] **Superglobals** `$_GET`, `$_POST`, `$_REQUEST`, `$_SERVER`, `$_SESSION`, `$_COOKIE`, `$_FILES` are always available in any scope.
- [x] **`htmlspecialchars()`** prevents **XSS** — always use it before echoing user input.
- [x] **`filter_var($email, FILTER_VALIDATE_EMAIL)`** is the **authoritative** email format check.
- [x] **GET vs POST:** GET is for non-sensitive, retrievable data; POST is for sensitive/large data.
- [x] **Never trust the client** — Always re-validate on the server even if JS validation passes.
- [x] **Form `onsubmit="return validate()"`** — The `return` keyword is **mandatory** to block submission.
- [x] **JS Form API:** `document.forms["formName"]["fieldName"].value` to read field values.
- [x] **Regular expressions** for validation: `/^[^\s@]+@[^\s@]+\.[^\s@]+$/` for email, `/^[0-9]{10}$/` for 10-digit phone.
- [x] **XAMPP/WAMP stack** uses **Apache + MySQL + PHP** — port **80** for HTTP, **443** for HTTPS.
- [x] **PHP file structure:** Place project in `htdocs` (XAMPP) or `/var/www/html` (Linux) to make it accessible via `http://localhost/`.
- [x] **Three-tier separation:** HTML (structure) $\rightarrow$ CSS (presentation) $\rightarrow$ JS/PHP (behavior/logic).

